Modelling

Data Preprocessing

vol_mean = mean(NSEI_drp$emp_vol,na.rm=TRUE)
vol_sd = sd(NSEI_drp$emp_vol,na.rm=TRUE)
NSEI_drp$vol_stnd <- (NSEI_drp$emp_vol - vol_mean )/vol_sd

gk_vol_mean = mean(NSEI_drp$gk_vol,na.rm=TRUE)
gk_vol_sd = sd(NSEI_drp$gk_vol,na.rm=TRUE)
NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd <- (NSEI_drp$emp_vol - gk_vol_mean )/gk_vol_sd

vol_mean_snp500 = mean(NSEI_drp$emp_vol_snp500,na.rm=TRUE)
vol_sd_snp500 = sd(NSEI_drp$emp_vol_snp500,na.rm=TRUE)
NSEI_drp$vol_stnd_snp500 <- (NSEI_drp$emp_vol_snp500 - vol_mean_snp500 )/vol_sd_snp500

gk_vol_mean_snp500 = mean(NSEI_drp$gk_vol_snp500)
gk_vol_sd_snp500 = sd(NSEI_drp$gk_vol_snp500)
NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd_snp500 <- (NSEI_drp$gk_vol_snp500 - gk_vol_mean_snp500 )/gk_vol_sd_snp500

vol_mean_gold = mean(NSEI_drp$emp_vol_gold)
vol_sd_gold = sd(NSEI_drp$emp_vol_gold)
NSEI_drp$vol_stnd_gold <- (NSEI_drp$emp_vol_gold - vol_mean_gold )/vol_sd_gold

gk_vol_mean_gold = mean(NSEI_drp$gk_vol_gold)
gk_vol_sd_gold = sd(NSEI_drp$gk_vol_gold)
NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd_gold <- (NSEI_drp$gk_vol_gold - gk_vol_mean_gold )/gk_vol_sd_gold
X = cbind.data.frame(Intercept=rep(1,n)
                     ,vol_stnd=NSEI_drp$vol_stnd
                     ,vol_stnd_snp500 = NSEI_drp$vol_stnd_snp500
                     ,vol_stnd_gold = NSEI_drp$vol_stnd_gold
                     ,gk_vol_stnd= NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd
                     ,gk_vol_stnd_snp500 = NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd_snp500
                     ,gk_vol_stnd_gold = NSEI_drp$gk_vol_stnd_gold
)


X = as.matrix(X)
y = NSEI_drp$rt
n=nrow(X)

Splitting the train and test

set.seed(231)
train_size = floor(n*0.80)
id <- sort(sample(1:n,train_size,replace = F))
X_train = X[id,]
X_test = X[-id,]
y_train = y[id]
y_test = y[-id]
mu = 2 ## 2% thresh hold
p = ncol(X)
p
## [1] 7
## Fit with Cauchy prior on beta
start_par = c(rep(0,p),0.1)
fit_cauchy <- optim(par = start_par,
                    fn = nlp_gpd_cauchy_prior,
                    y = y_train, X = X_train, mu = mu,
                    method = "BFGS",
                    control = list(maxit = 1000))

# Results
# Extract estimated parameters
par_hat <- fit_cauchy$par
beta_hat_cauchy <- fit_cauchy$par[1:p]
beta_hat_cauchy
## [1]  0.1493775  0.4103567 -0.1256704 -0.1447779  0.3413986  0.2436512  0.1437902
xi_hat_cauchy <- fit_cauchy$par[p + 1]
xi_hat_cauchy
## [1] -0.2900331
eta_cauchy = X_test%*%beta_hat_cauchy
sigma_cauchy = exp(eta_cauchy)
y_pred_cauchy = mu+(sigma_cauchy/(1-xi_hat_cauchy))
rmse_cauchy_scr = sqrt(mean((y_pred_cauchy-y_test)^2))
rmse_cauchy_scr
## [1] 1.426048
# Compute negative log-likelihood (without prior)
nll_value <- neg_log_lik_gpd(par = par_hat
                             , y = y_train
                             , X = X_train
                             , mu = mu)
# Number of estimated parameters
k <- length(par_hat)

# Number of observations
n <- length(y_train)

# AIC and BIC
aic_cauchy <- 2 * k + 2 * nll_value
bic_cauchy <- log(n) * k + 2 * nll_value

cat("AIC:", aic_cauchy, "\n")
## AIC: 281.1154
cat("BIC:", bic_cauchy, "\n")
## BIC: 305.2537

Fit with Lasso beta

GPD regression MLE with L1 regularisation (LASSO) on beta using 5-fold cross-validation

lambda_grid <- 10^seq(-2, 2, length.out = 50)

cv_result <- cv_gpd_lasso(y = y_train, X = X_train
                          , mu = mu
                          , lambda_grid = lambda_grid
                          , k = 5)
cat("Best lambda:", cv_result$best_lambda, "\n")
## Best lambda: 10.48113
# Final fit
fit_lasso <- fit_gpd_lasso(lambda = cv_result$best_lambda
                           , y = y_train
                           , X = X_train, mu = mu)
cat("Estimated beta:", fit_lasso$par[1:p], "\n")
## Estimated beta: 0.0215421 0.5175039 -0.0003677349 -0.0001579481 0.0009431253 0.1628554 0.03453261
cat("Estimated xi:", fit_lasso$par[p + 1], "\n")
## Estimated xi: -0.1547817
beta_hat_lasso <- fit_lasso$par[1:p]
beta_hat_lasso
## [1]  0.0215420970  0.5175039334 -0.0003677349 -0.0001579481  0.0009431253
## [6]  0.1628554039  0.0345326118
xi_hat_lasso <- fit_lasso$par[p + 1]
xi_hat_lasso
## [1] -0.1547817
eta_lasso = X_test%*%beta_hat_lasso
sigma_lasso = exp(eta_lasso)
y_pred_lasso = mu+(sigma_lasso/(1-xi_hat_lasso))
rmse_lasso_scr = sqrt(mean((y_pred_lasso-y_test)^2))
rmse_lasso_scr
## [1] 1.770609
# Extract estimated parameters
par_hat <- fit_lasso$par
beta_hat <- par_hat[1:ncol(X_train)]
xi_hat <- par_hat[ncol(X_train) + 1]

# Compute the negative log-likelihood (WITHOUT L1 penalty)
nll_value <- neg_log_lik_gpd(par = par_hat, y = y_train, X = X_train, mu = mu)

# Degrees of freedom (number of non-zero betas + 1 for xi)
k <- sum(beta_hat != 0) + 1

# Sample size
n <- length(y_train)

# Compute AIC and BIC
aic_lasso <- 2 * k + 2 * nll_value
bic_lasso <- log(n) * k + 2 * nll_value

# Print results
cat("AIC (Lasso):", aic_lasso, "\n")
## AIC (Lasso): 289.2343
cat("BIC (Lasso):", bic_lasso, "\n")
## BIC (Lasso): 313.3725

GPD regression with Zellner’s g-prior on beta using 5-fold cross-validation

g_grid <- 10^seq(-2, 2, length.out = 50)
cv_result <- cv_gpd_gprior(y = y_train, X = X_train
                           , mu = mu, g_grid = g_grid)
cat("Best g:", cv_result$best_g, "\n")
## Best g: 2.811769
# Final fit
fit_gprior <- fit_gpd_gprior(
  g_scale = cv_result$best_g,
  y = y_train,
  X = X_train,
  mu = mu
)


beta_hat_gprior <- fit_gprior$par[1:p]
xi_hat_gprior <- fit_gprior$par[p + 1]
eta_gprior = X_test%*%beta_hat_gprior
sigma_gprior = exp(eta_gprior)
y_pred_gprior = mu+(sigma_gprior/(1-xi_hat_gprior))
rmse_gprior_scr = sqrt(mean((y_pred_gprior-y_test)^2))

# Extract parameter estimates
par_hat <- fit_gprior$par

# Compute the negative log-likelihood (not the posterior!)
nll_value <- neg_log_lik_gpd(par = par_hat, y = y_train, X = X_train, mu = mu)

# Degrees of freedom: all betas + xi
k <- length(par_hat)

# Sample size
n <- length(y_train)

# Compute AIC and BIC
aic_gprior <- 2 * k + 2 * nll_value
bic_gprior <- log(n) * k + 2 * nll_value

# Print results
cat("AIC (g-prior):", aic_gprior, "\n")
## AIC (g-prior): 285.9076
cat("BIC (g-prior):", bic_gprior, "\n")
## BIC (g-prior): 310.0458

Consolidating results

rmse = c(rmse_cauchy_scr=rmse_cauchy_scr
         ,rmse_lasso_scr=rmse_lasso_scr
         ,rmse_ridge_scr=rmse_ridge_scr
         ,rmse_gprior_scr=rmse_gprior_scr)


aic = c(aic_cauchy=aic_cauchy
        ,aic_lasso=aic_lasso
        ,aic_ridge=aic_ridge
        ,aic_gprior=aic_gprior)


bic = c(bic_cauchy=bic_cauchy
        ,bic_lasso=bic_lasso
        ,bic_ridge=bic_ridge
        ,bic_gprior=bic_gprior)

eval_metrics = cbind.data.frame(rmse,aic,bic)

The Cauchy prior outperform others.

Prediction with Cauchy Prior

eta_0 = X%*%beta_hat_cauchy
sigma_0 = exp(eta_0)
y_0_cauchy = mu+(sigma_0/(1-xi_hat_cauchy)) ## E(y| y >2,x0)

Sy = (1-((xi_hat_cauchy*(5-mu))/sigma_0))^(1/xi_hat_cauchy) ## P(y>5 | y>2,x0)

predict_results <- cbind.data.frame(X,y,y_0_cauchy,Sy)

predict_results <- cbind.data.frame(NSEI_drp,y,y_0_cauchy,Sy)
library(ggplot2)

# Step 1: Fit model
mod <- lm(log10(y) ~ log10(y_0_cauchy), data = predict_results)

# Step 2: Get prediction interval (on log scale to match your plot)
pred_df <- predict(
  mod,
  newdata = predict_results,
  interval = "prediction",
  level = 0.95
)

# Step 3: Combine with data
predict_results$fit <- pred_df[, "fit"]
predict_results$lwr <- pred_df[, "lwr"]
predict_results$upr <- pred_df[, "upr"]

# Step 4: Plot with geom_ribbon for prediction interval
ggplot(predict_results, aes(x = y_0_cauchy, y = y, colour = emp_vol)) +
  # Prediction interval ribbon
  geom_ribbon(
  aes(
    x = y_0_cauchy,
    ymin = 10^lwr,
    ymax = 10^upr
  ),
  inherit.aes = FALSE,
  data = predict_results,
  fill = "grey70",
  alpha = 0.3)+
  geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 0.8, shape = 16) +
  geom_line(
    aes(y = 10^fit),
    colour = "black",
    linetype = "dashed",
    size = 1
  ) +
  scale_colour_gradientn(
    colours = c("blue", "skyblue", "yellow", "orange", "red"),
    name = "Empirical\nVolatility"
  ) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  scale_y_log10() +
  labs(
    title = "",
    x = expression("log Fitted Tail Loss: "~~log(hat(y)["Cauchy"])),
    y = "log Observed Tail Loss"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 15) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 16, hjust = 0.5),
    axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
    legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey85"),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),

Fitted Mean Tail Loss vs Observed Market Loss (Log-Scale)

# 1. Fit the model
mod2 <- lm(Sy ~ emp_vol, data = predict_results)

# 2. Get prediction interval
pred_df2 <- predict(
  mod2,
  newdata = predict_results,
  interval = "prediction",
  level = 0.95
)

# 3. Bind predictions to data
predict_results$fit2 <- pred_df2[, "fit"]
predict_results$lwr2 <- pred_df2[, "lwr"]
predict_results$upr2 <- pred_df2[, "upr"]

# 4. Plot with predictive interval ribbon
ggplot(predict_results, aes(x = emp_vol, y = Sy, colour = emp_vol_snp500)) +
  geom_ribbon(
    aes(
      x = emp_vol,
      ymin = lwr2,
      ymax = upr2
    ),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    fill = "grey70",
    alpha = 0.3
  ) +
  geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 0.8, shape = 16) +
  geom_line(
    aes(y = fit2),
    colour = "black",
    linetype = "dashed",
    size = 1
  ) +
  scale_colour_gradientn(
    colours = c("blue", "skyblue", "yellow", "orange", "red"),
    name = "Volatility of\nS&P 500"
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    limits = c(0, 1),
    breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1),
    labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "",
    x = "NSE Empirical Volatility",
    y = expression("Probability : " * P(Y > 5 ~ "|" ~ Y > 2 ~ ", x"[0]))
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 15) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 16, hjust = 0.5),
    axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
    legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey85"),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(colour = "black", fill = NA, size = 1)
  )
